# How can the United Nations help to ensure a lasting peace between Ukraine and Russia?

## Summary
The United Nations (UN) can help ensure a just and lasting peace between Ukraine and Russia by facilitating peace negotiations. Gen. Mark Milley, the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, recently suggested that both sides need to reach a mutual recognition that a military victory is not achievable and to turn to other means <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font>. The U.S. is nudging Ukraine to show a greater willingness to consider peace talks with Russia <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font>. However, Ukraine has denied being under Western pressure to negotiate with Russia and insists that talks can only be held if Russia relinquishes all occupied territories <font color=#FF3399>[3]</font>. The UN could help to facilitate these peace talks so that both sides can reach a political settlement to end the war <font color=#FF3399>[4, 5]</font>.

